{"title_page": "Assassin's Creed Chronicles", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|Assassin's Creed: Alta\u00efr's Chronicles}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox video game\n|title = Assassin's Creed Chronicles\n| image = Assassin's Creed Chronicles cover art.jpg\n| caption = Cover art featuring the three Assassins: Arbaaz Mir, [[Shao Jun]], and Nikolai Orelov\n| developer = [[Climax Studios]]\n| publisher = [[Ubisoft]]\n| director = \n| producer = \n| designer = Matt Duff\n| programmer = Ben Potton\n| artist = Neale Williams\n| writer = \n| composer = {{Unbulleted list|Aaron Miller|[[Mark Rutherford (composer)|Mark Rutherford]]}}\n| series = ''[[Assassin's Creed]]''\n| engine = [[Unreal Engine 3]]\n| platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[Microsoft Windows]]|[[PlayStation 4]]|[[Xbox One]]|[[PlayStation Vita]]}}\n| released = '''Microsoft Windows''', '''PlayStation 4''', '''Xbox One'''{{vgrelease|WW|April 21, 2015 <small>(China)</small>|WW|January 12, 2016 <small>(India)</small><ref name=\"Russia-India-Trilogy-release\">{{cite web |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles Trilogy Pack Coming to PS4 & PS Vita, India and Russia Episodes Dated |url=http://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2015/12/08/assassins-creed-chronicles-trilogy-pack-coming-ps4-ps-vita-india-russia-episodes-dated/ |work=[[PlayStation LifeStyle.net]] |date=December 8, 2015 |access-date=December 18, 2015 |first=Jason |last=Dunning |publisher=Evolve Media, LLC}}</ref>|WW|February 9, 2016 <small>(Russia & Trilogy Pack)</small><ref name=\"Russia-India-Trilogy-release\" />}}'''PlayStation Vita'''{{Video game release|WW|April 5, 2016<ref name=\"Russia-India-Trilogy-release\" />}}\n| genre = [[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]], [[Stealth game|stealth]]\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]]\n}}\n\n'''''Assassin's Creed Chronicles''''' is a sub-series of video games in the ''[[Assassin's Creed]]'' franchise. The series consists of three games developed by [[Climax Studios]] and published by [[Ubisoft]]. The games feature new protagonists and a design that is new to the franchise, a [[2.5D#2.5D platform games|2.5D]] world inspired by traditional brush paintings. The first entry, ''Assassin's Creed: China'', was released on April 21, 2015, on [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]]. The second entry, ''Assassin's Creed: India'', was released on January 12, 2016 on the same platforms. The last game, ''Assassin's Creed: Russia'', was released on February 9, 2016.<ref name=\"Trilogy Announcement\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/03/31/assassins-creed-chronicles-trilogy-announced |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles Trilogy Announced |work=[[IGN]] |date=March 31, 2014 |access-date=March 31, 2014 |first=Alex |last=Osborn |publisher=[[Ziff Davis, LLC]]}}</ref>\n\n==Gameplay==\nThe games are [[2.5D (visual perception)|2.5D]] side scrolling platformers.<ref name=\"Trilogy Announcement\" /> The games feature a large array of weapons such as secret shoe blade, rope darts, and daggers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/first-assassin-s-creed-2-5d-game-launch-trailer-in/1100-6426765/|title= First Assassin's Creed 2.5D Game Launch Trailer|author= Eddie Makuch|publisher= Gamespot | date= April 20, 2015 |accessdate= December 18, 2015}}</ref> Players must control the protagonist, and navigate through the environment. Players can use stealth tactics such as hiding from enemies in shadows and can climb areas that are highlighted with more color.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/04/02/assassins-creed-chronicles-bringing-the-series-to-2d|title= Assassin's Creed Chronicles:Bringing the series to 2D|author= Marty Sliva|publisher=[[IGN]] | date= April 2, 2015 |accessdate= December 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China''===\n''China'' takes place after the short film ''[[Assassin's Creed: Embers]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Phillips|first1=Tom|title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India and Russia finally get release dates|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2015-12-09-assassins-creed-chronicles-india-and-russia-finally-get-release-dates|website=Eurogamer.net|accessdate=21 July 2017}}</ref> The game takes place in 1526 China and focuses on the female protagonist, [[Shao Jun]]. After being trained by legendary Italian assassin [[Ezio Auditore da Firenze]], Shao Jun returns to her homeland to exact vengeance against the Templar group [[Eight Tigers]], who wiped out the Chinese brotherhood. Shao Jun's quest takes her through [[Macau]], [[Nan'an, Fujian|Nan'an]], the [[Forbidden City]] and the [[Great Wall]], as she kills the Tigers one by one and finally assassinates the final target, Zhang Yong. Years later, Shao Jun, who becomes an Assassin Mentor and has rebuilt the brotherhood, plots the assassination of [[Jiajing Emperor]] by sending him an elixir of life, which is actually lethal mercury. The episode has 12 levels.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Patrick|title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles cuts away the series' fat in its promising debut|url=http://www.avclub.com/article/assassins-creed-chronicles-cuts-away-series-fat-it-218726|website=The A.V. Club|accessdate=20 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India''===\n''India'' takes place in 1841 India and features the male protagonist, Arbaaz Mir from graphic novel [[Assassin's Creed: Brahman]]. While the [[Sikh Empire]] was at war with the [[British East India Company|East India Company]], a Master Templar arrives with a mysterious item that used to belong to the Assassin Order. Mir must discover why he has come, steal back the item, and protect his friends and his lover. Some of the weapons introduced are a typical [[Mughal Empire|Mughal]] and [[Dravidian peoples|Dravidian]] [[Hinduism|Hindu]] sword resembling an [[Aruval]] of [[Tamil Nadu|Tamil Nadu]], [[Urumi]] from [[South India]], a concealed [[Katara (dagger)|Katara]] with [[Bagh naka]], and [[Chakram]], smoke bombs for stealth and distraction. A [[Slingshot]] with rock pellets has also been added.\n\n===Secret ending===\nA secret ending can be unlocked in ''Chronicles: Russia'' by inputting hidden codes found throughout all 3 games. The ending takes place in present day, where Templar agent Juhani Otso Berg meets up with the Head of Operations at Abstergo Industries, Laetitia England. Berg, who [[Assassin's Creed Rogue|recently studied the memory of Assassin-turned-Templar Shay Cormac]] to learn the location of the Precursor box (an artifact seen throughout all three Chronicles episodes), had brought the box to England, who instructed him to take it to \u00c1lvaro Gram\u00e1tica in secret. Gram\u00e1tica claims the box to be instrumental in helping him with the Phoenix Project.\n\n==Development and release==\n''China'' was announced in September 2014 as part of the season pass for ''[[Assassin's Creed Unity]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/09/22/assassins-creed-unity-dlc-includes-new-story-in-china|title= Assassin's Creed Unity DLC Included New Story in China|publisher= [[IGN]] |date=September 22, 2014 |accessdate = March 31, 2015| url-status=live}}</ref> On March 31, 2015, it was announced that ''China'' was part of a trilogy, with ''India'' and ''Russia'' to be released at a later time. The trilogy was developed by [[Climax Studios]] in association with [[Ubisoft Montreal]].<ref name=\"Trilogy Announcement\" /> ''China'' was released on April 21, 2015 for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]]. ''China'' is the first title in the franchise to utilize Epic Games' [[Unreal Engine 3]].\n\nOn December 8, 2015, Ubisoft announced that ''India'' would be released on January 12, 2016 and ''Russia'' would be released on February 9, 2016 alongside a collection of the three games titled ''Trilogy Pack''. A [[PlayStation Vita]] version of the Trilogy Pack was released on April 5, 2016.<ref name=\"Russia-India-Trilogy-release\" />\n\n==Reception==\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China''===\n{{VG reviews\n| MC = (PC) 67/100<ref name=\"MCPCChina\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/assassins-creed-chronicles-china |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China for PC Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(PS4) 69/100<ref name=\"MCPS4China\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/assassins-creed-chronicles-china |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China for PlayStation 4 Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(XONE) 67/100<ref name=\"MCXONEChina\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/assassins-creed-chronicles-china |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China for Xbox ONe Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China'' received \"mixed or average\" reviews from critics upon release, according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MCPCChina\"/><ref name=\"MCPS4China\"/><ref name=\"MCXONEChina\"/>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India''===\n{{VG reviews\n| MC = (PC) 63/100<ref name=\"MCPCIndia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/assassins-creed-chronicles-india |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India for PC Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(PS4) 63/100<ref name=\"MCPS4India\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/assassins-creed-chronicles-india |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India for PlayStation 4 Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(XONE) 64/100<ref name=\"MCXONEIndia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/assassins-creed-chronicles-india |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India for Xbox One Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India'' received \"mixed or average\" reviews from critics upon release, according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MCPCIndia\"/><ref name=\"MCPS4India\"/><ref name=\"MCXONEIndia\"/>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia''===\n{{VG reviews\n| MC = (PC) 53/100<ref name=\"MCPCRussia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/assassins-creed-chronicles-russia |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia for PC Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(PS4) 60/100<ref name=\"MCPS4Russia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/assassins-creed-chronicles-russia |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia for PlayStation 4 Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(XONE) 62/100<ref name=\"MCXONERussia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/assassins-creed-chronicles-russia |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia for Xbox One Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia'' received \"mixed or average\" reviews from critics upon release, according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MCPCRussia\"/><ref name=\"MCPS4Russia\"/><ref name=\"MCXONERussia\"/>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal bar|Video games}}\n\n{{Assassin's Creed}}\n\n[[Category:2015 video games]]\n[[Category:Assassin's Creed]]\n[[Category:Action-adventure games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation Network games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation Vita games]]\n[[Category:Side-scrolling video games]]\n[[Category:Single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Stealth video games]]\n[[Category:Ubisoft games]]\n[[Category:Unreal Engine games]]\n[[Category:Video games featuring female protagonists]]\n[[Category:Video games with historical settings]]\n[[Category:Video game spin-offs]]\n[[Category:Video games set in China]]\n[[Category:Video games set in India]]\n[[Category:Video games set in Moscow]]\n[[Category:Video games set in Russia]]\n[[Category:Video games set in the Russian Empire]]\n[[Category:British India in fiction]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Xbox One games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Assassin's Creed: Alta\u00efr's Chronicles}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox video game\n|title = Assassin's Creed Chronicles\n| image = Assassin's Creed Chronicles cover art.jpg\n| caption = Cover art featuring the three Assassins: Arbaaz Mir, [[Shao Jun]], and Nikolai Orelov\n| developer = [[Climax Studios]]\n| publisher = [[Ubisoft]]\n| director = \n| producer = \n| designer = Matt Duff\n| programmer = Ben Potton\n| artist = Neale Williams\n| writer = \n| composer = {{Unbulleted list|Aaron Miller|[[Mark Rutherford (composer)|Mark Rutherford]]}}\n| series = ''[[Assassin's Creed]]''\n| engine = [[Unreal Engine 3]]\n| platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[Microsoft Windows]]|[[PlayStation 4]]|[[Xbox One]]|[[PlayStation Vita]]}}\n| released = '''Microsoft Windows''', '''PlayStation 4''', '''Xbox One'''{{vgrelease|WW|April 21, 2015 <small>(China)</small>|WW|January 12, 2016 <small>(India)</small><ref name=\"Russia-India-Trilogy-release\">{{cite web |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles Trilogy Pack Coming to PS4 & PS Vita, India and Russia Episodes Dated |url=http://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2015/12/08/assassins-creed-chronicles-trilogy-pack-coming-ps4-ps-vita-india-russia-episodes-dated/ |work=[[PlayStation LifeStyle.net]] |date=December 8, 2015 |access-date=December 18, 2015 |first=Jason |last=Dunning |publisher=Evolve Media, LLC}}</ref>|WW|February 9, 2016 <small>(Russia & Trilogy Pack)</small><ref name=\"Russia-India-Trilogy-release\" />}}'''PlayStation Vita'''{{Video game release|WW|April 5, 2016<ref name=\"Russia-India-Trilogy-release\" />}}\n| genre = [[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]], [[Stealth game|stealth]]\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]]\n}}\n\n'''''Assassin's Creed Chronicles''''' is a sub-series of video games in the ''[[Assassin's Creed]]'' franchise. The series consists of three games developed by [[Climax Studios]] and published by [[Ubisoft]]. The games feature new protagonists and a design that is new to the franchise, a [[2.5D#2.5D platform games|2.5D]] world inspired by traditional brush paintings. The first entry, ''Assassin's Creed: China'', was released on April 21, 2015, on [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]]. The second entry, ''Assassin's Creed: India'', was released on January 12, 2016 on the same platforms. The last game, ''Assassin's Creed: Russia'', was released on February 9, 2016.<ref name=\"Trilogy Announcement\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/03/31/assassins-creed-chronicles-trilogy-announced |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles Trilogy Announced |work=[[IGN]] |date=March 31, 2014 |access-date=March 31, 2014 |first=Alex |last=Osborn |publisher=[[Ziff Davis, LLC]]}}</ref>\n\n==Gameplay==\nThe games are [[2.5D (visual perception)|2.5D]] side scrolling platformers.<ref name=\"Trilogy Announcement\" /> The games feature a large array of weapons such as secret shoe blade, rope darts, and daggers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/first-assassin-s-creed-2-5d-game-launch-trailer-in/1100-6426765/|title= First Assassin's Creed 2.5D Game Launch Trailer|author= Eddie Makuch|publisher= Gamespot | date= April 20, 2015 |accessdate= December 18, 2015}}</ref> Players must control the protagonist, and navigate through the environment. Players can use stealth tactics such as hiding from enemies in shadows and can climb areas that are highlighted with more color.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/04/02/assassins-creed-chronicles-bringing-the-series-to-2d|title= Assassin's Creed Chronicles:Bringing the series to 2D|author= Marty Sliva|publisher=[[IGN]] | date= April 2, 2015 |accessdate= December 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China''===\n''China'' takes place after the short film ''[[Assassin's Creed: Embers]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Phillips|first1=Tom|title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India and Russia finally get release dates|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2015-12-09-assassins-creed-chronicles-india-and-russia-finally-get-release-dates|website=Eurogamer.net|accessdate=21 July 2017}}</ref> The game takes place in 1526 China and focuses on the female protagonist, [[Shao Jun]]. After being trained by legendary Italian assassin [[Ezio Auditore da Firenze]], Shao Jun returns to her homeland to exact vengeance against the Templar group [[Eight Tigers]], who wiped out the Chinese brotherhood. Shao Jun's quest takes her through [[Macau]], [[Nan'an, Fujian|Nan'an]], the [[Forbidden City]] and the [[Great Wall]], as she kills the Tigers one by one and finally assassinates the final target, Zhang Yong. Years later, Shao Jun, who becomes an Assassin Mentor and has rebuilt the brotherhood, plots the assassination of [[Jiajing Emperor]] by sending him an elixir of life, which is actually lethal mercury. The episode has 12 levels.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Patrick|title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles cuts away the series' fat in its promising debut|url=http://www.avclub.com/article/assassins-creed-chronicles-cuts-away-series-fat-it-218726|website=The A.V. Club|accessdate=20 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India''===\n''India'' takes place in 1841 India and features the male protagonist, Arbaaz Mir from graphic novel [[Assassin's Creed: Brahman]]. While the [[Sikh Empire]] was at war with the [[British East India Company|East India Company]], a Master Templar arrives with a mysterious item that used to belong to the Assassin Order. Mir must discover why he has come, steal back the item, and protect his friends and his lover. Some of the weapons introduced are a typical [[Mughal Empire|Mughal]] and [[Dravidian peoples|Dravidian]] [[Hinduism|Hindu]] sword resembling an [[Aruval]] of [[Tamil Nadu|Tamil Nadu]], [[Urumi]] from [[South India]], a concealed [[Katara (dagger)|Katara]] with [[Bagh naka]], and [[Chakram]], smoke bombs for stealth and distraction. A [[Slingshot]] with rock pellets has also been added.\n\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia''===\n''Russia'' takes place in 1918 Russia during the aftermath of the [[October Revolution]] and features male protagonist Nikolai Orelov from comic book [[Assassin's Creed: The Fall|Assassin's Creed: Subject Four]]. Orelov wants to leave with his family, but is required to perform one last mission for the Assassin Order: infiltrate the house where the Tsar's family is being held by the [[Bolsheviks]], and steal an artifact that has been fought over by Assassins and Templars for centuries. Along the way, he witnesses the massacre of the Tsar [[Nicholas II]]'s children, but manages to save the grand duchess, [[Anastasia Nicolaievna Romanova|Anastasia]], who shares Shao Jun's memory. He must escape the Templars while protecting the artifact and Anastasia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JapuE16BPrY|title= Assassin's Creed Chronicles Announcement Trailer [US]|publisher= Ubisoft |date= March 31, 2014 |accessdate= March 31, 2014| url-status=live}}</ref> Nikolai uses a custom [[Berdan rifle]] fitted with a bayonet which can be used for melee combat with sniping capabilities, and a grapnel gun that can also produce electricity in order to short out electricity boxes, spotlights, lamp posts or kill unsuspecting enemies standing on water puddles. Anastasia also becomes a playable character with unique set of skills, including the Helix Blade.<ref>{{cite web|title=ASSASSIN'S CREED CHRONICLES: RUSSIA PC|url=http://store.ubi.com/upc/us/assassin-s-creed-chronicles--russia/57062ec488a7e316728b469e.html|website=Ubisoft|accessdate=26 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Secret ending===\nA secret ending can be unlocked in ''Chronicles: Russia'' by inputting hidden codes found throughout all 3 games. The ending takes place in present day, where Templar agent Juhani Otso Berg meets up with the Head of Operations at Abstergo Industries, Laetitia England. Berg, who [[Assassin's Creed Rogue|recently studied the memory of Assassin-turned-Templar Shay Cormac]] to learn the location of the Precursor box (an artifact seen throughout all three Chronicles episodes), had brought the box to England, who instructed him to take it to \u00c1lvaro Gram\u00e1tica in secret. Gram\u00e1tica claims the box to be instrumental in helping him with the Phoenix Project.\n\n==Development and release==\n''China'' was announced in September 2014 as part of the season pass for ''[[Assassin's Creed Unity]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/09/22/assassins-creed-unity-dlc-includes-new-story-in-china|title= Assassin's Creed Unity DLC Included New Story in China|publisher= [[IGN]] |date=September 22, 2014 |accessdate = March 31, 2015| url-status=live}}</ref> On March 31, 2015, it was announced that ''China'' was part of a trilogy, with ''India'' and ''Russia'' to be released at a later time. The trilogy was developed by [[Climax Studios]] in association with [[Ubisoft Montreal]].<ref name=\"Trilogy Announcement\" /> ''China'' was released on April 21, 2015 for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]]. ''China'' is the first title in the franchise to utilize Epic Games' [[Unreal Engine 3]].\n\nOn December 8, 2015, Ubisoft announced that ''India'' would be released on January 12, 2016 and ''Russia'' would be released on February 9, 2016 alongside a collection of the three games titled ''Trilogy Pack''. A [[PlayStation Vita]] version of the Trilogy Pack was released on April 5, 2016.<ref name=\"Russia-India-Trilogy-release\" />\n\n==Reception==\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China''===\n{{VG reviews\n| MC = (PC) 67/100<ref name=\"MCPCChina\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/assassins-creed-chronicles-china |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China for PC Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(PS4) 69/100<ref name=\"MCPS4China\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/assassins-creed-chronicles-china |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China for PlayStation 4 Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(XONE) 67/100<ref name=\"MCXONEChina\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/assassins-creed-chronicles-china |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China for Xbox ONe Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: China'' received \"mixed or average\" reviews from critics upon release, according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MCPCChina\"/><ref name=\"MCPS4China\"/><ref name=\"MCXONEChina\"/>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India''===\n{{VG reviews\n| MC = (PC) 63/100<ref name=\"MCPCIndia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/assassins-creed-chronicles-india |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India for PC Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(PS4) 63/100<ref name=\"MCPS4India\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/assassins-creed-chronicles-india |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India for PlayStation 4 Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(XONE) 64/100<ref name=\"MCXONEIndia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/assassins-creed-chronicles-india |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India for Xbox One Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: India'' received \"mixed or average\" reviews from critics upon release, according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MCPCIndia\"/><ref name=\"MCPS4India\"/><ref name=\"MCXONEIndia\"/>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n===''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia''===\n{{VG reviews\n| MC = (PC) 53/100<ref name=\"MCPCRussia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/assassins-creed-chronicles-russia |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia for PC Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(PS4) 60/100<ref name=\"MCPS4Russia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/assassins-creed-chronicles-russia |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia for PlayStation 4 Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref><br />(XONE) 62/100<ref name=\"MCXONERussia\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/assassins-creed-chronicles-russia |title=Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia for Xbox One Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Assassin's Creed Chronicles: Russia'' received \"mixed or average\" reviews from critics upon release, according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=\"MCPCRussia\"/><ref name=\"MCPS4Russia\"/><ref name=\"MCXONERussia\"/>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal bar|Video games}}\n\n{{Assassin's Creed}}\n\n[[Category:2015 video games]]\n[[Category:Assassin's Creed]]\n[[Category:Action-adventure games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation Network games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation Vita games]]\n[[Category:Side-scrolling video games]]\n[[Category:Single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Stealth video games]]\n[[Category:Ubisoft games]]\n[[Category:Unreal Engine games]]\n[[Category:Video games featuring female protagonists]]\n[[Category:Video games with historical settings]]\n[[Category:Video game spin-offs]]\n[[Category:Video games set in China]]\n[[Category:Video games set in India]]\n[[Category:Video games set in Moscow]]\n[[Category:Video games set in Russia]]\n[[Category:Video games set in the Russian Empire]]\n[[Category:British India in fiction]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the Unite